    "_comment_executionWitness": "Output of Besu's `debug_executionWitness`, one entry per block in canonical block-range order. Each entry contains `state` (state-trie nodes touched), `keys` (storage keys accessed), `codes` (accessed contract bytecode), and `headers` (recent block headers for the BLOCKHASH opcode). The first entry's `headers` must contain exactly one parent header whose block hash equals the first block's parentHash; that header anchors `parentBlockHash` and provides the starting state root.",
